[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simplified, illustrative implementation of the concepts from Recipe 15.9. It demonstrates the shape of a radiation therapy adaptive planning system using offline reinforcement learning. It is absolutely not production-ready, not clinically validated, and not something you would deploy anywhere near a treatment machine. The physics is simplified. The tumor dynamics are a toy model. The dose calculations are approximations of approximations. Think of it as a learning tool: code you can run to understand how the RL pieces fit together for sequential treatment adaptation. A starting point for research, not a destination for clinical use.
